
[1]hourglass

   HOUR'GLASS, n. our'glass. A chronometer that measures the flux of time
   by the running of sand from one glass vessel to another, through a
   small aperture. Instead of sand, dry egg shells pulverized are
   sometimes used. The quantity of sand may be so proportioned as to
   measure an hour, a half hour, or a quarter.

   1. Space of time.
